# Coding Standards

## TypeScript (shared)
- Strict mode, no `any` in new code (prefer `unknown` or proper types)
- Use `class-validator` DTOs on API, Zod or manual validation on web
- No unused imports; run linter after edits

## API (NestJS)
- Feature modules: controller + service + dto + module per domain
- Always use `AuthGuard('jwt')` for protected routes
- Prisma `select` — pick only needed fields, never `include` full relations
- Return consistent shapes: `{ ok, data }` or throw NestJS exceptions
- Keep business logic in services, controllers are thin

## Web (Next.js)
- App Router, Server Components by default; `'use client'` only when needed
- API calls via `apiGetJson`/`apiFetchJson` from `lib/api.ts`
- Tailwind only, no inline styles; follow `docs/MARKETPLACE_UI_STYLE.md`
- Dark mode: always add `dark:` variants; never leave white surfaces in dark
- Components in `src/components/`, page-specific logic in page files

## Git
- No commits without explicit user request
- No force pushes, no --amend on pushed commits
